abstract: Russian news media report that security services killed 14 insurgents trying to smuggle people intent on joining Islamic State in Syria out of North Caucasus.
lead_paragraph: The men, accused of smuggling out fighters to join the Islamic State, were killed in two clashes with law enforcement agents, according to Russian news reports quoting a government statement..

headline.main: Russia Says It Killed 14 ISIS Recruiters in North Caucasus
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Europe; Russia: Security Services Kill 14 Linked to Smuggling of Fighters to Syria
